how do i decipher the spam filter evaluation code how do i find it stanford answers stanford university stanford answers how do i decipher the spam filter evaluation code how do i find it categories accounts and ids administrative applications anti virus and security computer operating systems connecting to the network desktop hardware and support email and calendar help desk restricted information on it services software at stanford stanford hospital and clinics telephones and cable tv unix systems and software web services user login login with your sunet id home how do i decipher the spam filter evaluation code how do i find it search this site spam has certain common traits that can be detected by the spam filter the evaluation code attached to each email lists the traits that apply to that particular email for example spammers often write their subject headings in capital letters if you see subj_all_caps in the evaluation code it means the system noticed this and considered it when deciding whether the email was spam the same is true when you see big_font or click_here_link in the evaluation code the system is noting and reporting elements in the message that are commonly seen in spam as well when you see rcvd_in_ it means the email is almost certainly spam because it was detected by a spam filtering system elsewhere and was reported to one of many web sites that monitor spam and track the various places spam comes from if you check the evaluation code you ll soon get a feel for what constitutes spam the spam filter evaluation code is listed in the internet headers to view the internet headers for a message right click on the highlighted message that you want to look at in the drop down menu click options the headers for your message appear in the internet headers box email viruses and spam stanford university 450 serra mall stanford california 94305 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints
